<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Vietnam is Russia's Close Partner, Says Chernomyrdin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, November 23 (Xinhua) -- Russian Prime Minister Viktor
Chernomyrdin said here today that Vietnam is Russia's close
partner.
</P>
<P>
Speaking to the Interfax Agency shortly before his upcoming
visit to Vietnam, he said that the economic and trade cooperation
between the two countries lags behind their political relations.
</P>
<P>
He said the priority of his visit is to promote the bilateral
economic and trade relations to a higher level.
</P>
<P>
Chernomyrdin said that he will meet his Vietnamese counterpart
Phan Van Khai and discuss with him ways to promote economic and
trade cooperation.
</P>
<P>
He added that the two countries would adjust their attitudes
toward the debt that Vietnam owes to Russia, which totals 17
billion U.S. dollars as agreed upon by both sides.
</P>
<P>
Chernomyrdin will leave here for Hanoi to start a three-day
visit to Vietnam later today. 
</P>
</TEXT>
