<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Crooked Accounting Under Fire </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, November 23 (Xinhua) -- Tanzanian Fiance
Minister Daniel Yona has expressed concern over dishonest and
unscrupulous accountants and auditors, calling for their removal
in the profession to restore credibility, press reports said
today.
</P>
<P>
Speaking during the 19th National Board of Accountants and
Auditors (NBAA) graduation ceremony in Dar es Salaam Saturday,
Yona said auditors and accountants need to be in the forefront in
the fighting against fiscal mismanagement.
</P>
<P>
"Accountants and auditors are supposed to be watchdogs but
unfortunately the game wardens have now become the poachers," he
said at the ceremony, which was officiated by President Benjamin
Mkapa.
</P>
<P>
It has become commonplace nowadays to hear a cashier, a book
keeper, an accountant clerk or even a Financial Controller
stealing from a firm. "We have been making losses for years," he
said.
</P>
<P>
The financial minister called on the accountants and auditors
to improve professional ethics and help the government in
fighting financial mismanagement and graft practices at their
workplaces.
</P>
<P>
"You should strive to eliminate fake accounts so as to boost the
status of your profession," he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
