<HEADLINE> Chinese Chen Wins Vietnam Badminton Championship </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, November 23 (Xinhua) -- Chen Gang of China beat
Indonesia's Alan Budi Kusuma in the final to take the men's
singles crown at the Vietnam Badminton Championships here on
Sunday.
</P>
<P>
He won the first set 15-6 but Kusuma fought back to take the
second 15-9.
</P>
<P>
Chen then took the decider 15-3 for his title and prevented the
Indonesians from completing a clean sweep of the golds.
</P>
<P>
All the other four titles were won by the Indonesians with top
seed women's singles player Susi Susanti effortlessly beating
runner-up Xu Huaiwen from China 11-4, 11-1, earning top points in
the last tournament of the year on the Grand Prix circuit.
</P>
<P>
In the men's doubles, Ricky Subagja and Rexy Mainaky defeated
South Korea's Yoo Yong-Sung and Lee Dong-Soo 15-11, 15-5.
</P>
<P>
In the women's doubles Rosiana Zelin and Eliza needed three
games to beat Isoliana Indarti and Renyana Lomban in an
all-Indonesian final 15-11, 12-15, 15-11.
</P>
<P>
Bambang Suprianto and Rosalina Riseu also clinched the top
prize for Indonesia in the mixed doubles, beating Lee Dong-Soo and
Park Soo-Yun of South Korea 15-5, 15-10. 
</P>
</TEXT>
