<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Three Speed Skating World Records Improved </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, November 23 (Xinhua) -- Japan's Manabu Horii and Jan
Bos of the Netherlands improved the men's 1000 meters world record
at the World Cup speed skating tournament in Calgary, Canada on
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Horii and Bos both clocked one minute 10.63 seconds. Horii held
the previous record of 1:11.67 which he set in 1996.
</P>
<P>
Canadian Catriona LeMay-Doan also broke two women's world
records when she clocked 37.90 seconds in the 500m and one minute
16.07 seconds in the 1000m.
</P>
<P>
The previous 500m record was 38.69 seconds, set by American
Bonnie Blair in 1995. The previous 1000m record was one minute
17.65 seconds, set in the Calgray Olympics in 1988 by Germany's
Christa Rothenburger. 
</P>
</TEXT>
