<HEADLINE> Man in Connection With Murder of Moro Arrested </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, November 23 (Xinhua) -- Greek police Saturday arrested
an Italian man convicted of involvement in the 1978 murder of
former Italian Prime Minister Aldo Moro.
</P>
<P>
Enrico Aristeidis Bianco, 45, was arrested in Aktio, Preveza,
northwestern Greece, where he was living on a yacht, Greek police
announced here today.
</P>
<P>
Bianco, a member of the Italian terrorist organization, the Red
Brigades, was living in Greece with a forged passport in the name
of Fulvio Folini.
</P>
<P>
He was sentenced in absentee to 10 years imprisonment for
complicity in the Moro killing.
</P>
<P>
Bianco will be questioned by the anti-terrorist service in
Athens and will be extradited to Italy. 
</P>
</TEXT>
