<HEADLINE> Blair to Hold Meeting with Sinn Fein Next Month </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, November 23 (Xinhua) -- British Northern Ireland
Minister Mo Mowlam said today Prime Minister Tony Blair would meet
with Northern Ireland republican leader Gerry Adams before
Christmas to discuss the peace process.
</P>
<P>
"Yes, they will meet before Christmas, I guess at (Downing
Street) Number 10, but we don't have a date yet," Mowlam told BBC
television.
</P>
<P>
The two would discuss the current multi-party peace process
seeking to end decades of tension between the troubled region's
Catholic and Protestant population, she added.
</P>
<P>
The talks will be the first meeting there since 1921 between a
British prime minister and a leader of Sinn Fein, political wing
of the outlawed Irish Republican Army (IRA). 
</P>
</TEXT>
