<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Italian President in Ethiopia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, November 23 (Xinhua) -- Italian President Oscar
Luigi Scalfaro arrived here today for a four-day official visit
in a bid to heal remaining wounds caused by Italy's occupation of
Ethiopia during World War two.
</P>
<P>
On arrival at the Bole international airport here, Scalfaro
was received by Ethiopian President Negasso Gidada.
</P>
<P>
Squares and avenues in Addis are bedecked with Italian and
Ethiopian flags and large crowds have turned out to line the
route from the airport to the city center.
</P>
<P>
President Scalfaro is the first Italian president who visits
Ethiopia. He will hold talks with Ethiopian Prime Minister Meles
Zenawi and President Negasso respectively tomorrow.
</P>
<P>
High on the agenda is discussion on the return of the Axum
Oblisque, a historical monument removed from northern Ethiopia on
the orders of the Italian fascist leader Benito Mussoloni during
the war, sources here said.
</P>
<P>
It currently stands outside the United Nations Food and
Agriculture Organization headquarters in Rome.
</P>
<P>
The two sides will also explore ways of enhancing investment
by Italian Private sector in the Ethiopian economy.
</P>
<P>
Scalfaro will address the Addis Ababa-based Organization of
African Unity on November 26 on "the contribution of Italy to
Euro-African relations on the eve of the 21st century."
</P>
<P>
Scalfaro, who was born in 1918, was elected Italian President
in 1992. 
</P>
</TEXT>
