<HEADLINE> China's Most Powerful International Travel Agencies Selected </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 24 (Xinhua) -- The Head Office of China
International Travel Service leads the 1996 list of the 100 most
powerful international travel agencies in China.
</P>
<P>
The second and third runner-ups are the Shanghai China
International Travel Service Co. Ltd.. and the Head Office of
China Travel Service.
</P>
<P>
The results of the selection process has been announced by the
China National Tourism Administration (CNTA).
</P>
<P>
According to a spokesman for CNTA, selection criteria included
the number of overseas tourists they handled, business turnover
and profits.
</P>
<P>
Travel agencies entitled to participate in the selection should
meet basic conditions including a sound internal management
system, reseasonable input and outstanding achievements in
international market promotion and in developing new tourist
programs, a good service quality guarantee system, and being free
from serious safety and quality accidents.
</P>
<P>
By 1996, there were 959 international travel agencies operating
across China, with business turnover averaging 22.28 million yuan
(about 2.68 million U.S. dollars) per agency.
</P>
<P>
Among them, 33 agencies each exceeded 100 million yuan in
business turnover, accounting for 3.6 percent of the total; 622
agencies each had a turnover between 1 million yuan to 22.28
million yuan, accounting for 68.5 percent of the total.  
</P>
</TEXT>
