<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Iranian Judiciary Urged Not to be Involved in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, November 24 (Xinhua) -- The Iranian judiciary bodies
were urged not to be involved in the political struggles among
the country's various factions, local daily Iran News reported
today.
</P>
<P>
"As a citizen, I expect the Judiciary to fulfill its duties
while demonstrating that it does not follow any particular
political line," Iranian Vice President for Legal and
Parliamentary Affairs Seyed Abdolvahed Musavi Lari said.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with Iran News published today, Lari blamed
the country's judiciary bodies for their manners in dealing
with the cases of Tehran municipality.
</P>
<P>
He doubted that political factors were taken into consideration
by the Judiciary when dealing with certain cases, he said, adding
that the judiciary officials must prove that the cases of Tehran
municipality are not politically motivated, he said.
</P>
<P>
Tehran Mayor Gholamhussein Karbaschi was charged with being
involved in some embezzlement cases. Some of his subordinates have
been arrested.
</P>
<P>
According to the judicial procedures, proof of the crime must
be established before any accusations are made and then the
suspect is informed of the accusations, Lari said.
</P>
<P>
But when dealing with these cases, the Judiciary's performance
was questioned because people were first arrested and asked to make
certain confessions before their crimes were proven, Lari noted.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that the Judiciary must deal with the Tehran
municipality cases according to the judicial procedures, saying
that "if proper procedures are ignored, the whole process will
become questionable."
</P>
<P>
According to the law, the vice president said, all the accused
must be released from solitary confinement and be tried at open
courts and the judge must investigate the files in a free
atmosphere.
</P>
<P>
The Iranian conservative factions suffered a disgraceful defeat
in the May presidential elections during which Mohammad Khatami
won a slide victory.
</P>
<P>
The leftist groups accused the conservatives of taking
retaliation to the defeat while dealing with the cases of Tehran
municipality. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
