<HEADLINE> Cyprus Urges Environmental Protection in Regional </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, November 24 (Xinhua) -- The countries in the Middle
East and Mediterranean region have been called upon to integrate
the goals of environmental protection into their economic and
social policy.
</P>
<P>
The call was made today by Cypriot Minister of Agriculture,
Natural Resources and Environment Andreas Mantovanis at the
opening of a regional workshop on "Sustainable Agriculture for
the Middle East and Mediterranean Countries".
</P>
<P>
Delegates from Israel, Greece, Italy, Egypt, Morocco, Yemen,
and Tunisia participated in the workshop, which is co-organized by
Cypriot Ministry of Agriculture, Natural Resources and
Environment, and the Israeli Ministry of Agriculture.
</P>
<P>
Mantovanis said Cyprus fully shares the concern that the
prevailing trends in the global food production and trade are
creating enormous stress and destruction to ecological environment.
</P>
<P>
If these developments are not put under control, they will
have irreversible consequences on natural resources, on which
agriculture relies, Mantovanis pointed out.
</P>
<P>
"Thus, we have to endorse the principles of sustainable
development, and to set in motion processes to integrate the
goals of environment conservation, into those of our economic and
social policy," the minister added.
</P>
<P>
The workshop is part of the existing cooperation program on
agriculture between Cyprus and Israel. 
</P>
</TEXT>
