<HEADLINE> Province Elects People's Congress Representatives (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, November 24 (Xinhua) -- Zhao Chunlin and his fellow
villagers arrived early at a plain courtyard, waiting for a solemn
moment.
</P>
<P>
On Nov. 20, polling day, Zhao was among voters who gathered to
elect deputies to the county people's congress in Langxi County in
east China's Anhui Province.
</P>
<P>
After an announcement by Chen Chaoyou, headmaster of Xingfu
Township Primary School and the voting organizer, the polling
started.
</P>
<P>
Zhao, 41, taking his elector's certificate, lined up to receive
a ballot. He drew marks behind the names of the two candidates in
his ballot, and then placed it into the slot in a red,
paper-wrapped box.
</P>
<P>
Zhao, who has participated in several elections for deputies of
the county people's congress, said that voters were enthusiastic
about electing deputies because of more rational procedures this
time.
</P>
<P>
"More importantly," he said, "deputies of previous county
people's congresses here have won the confidence of the people by
proposing the renovation of school buildings, raising teachers'
salaries, building flood-control facilities and developing the
local economy."
</P>
<P>
For voters' convenience, staff members in the electoral
district also offered five mobile boxes, each escorted by three
working members to collect ballots in villagers' homes.
</P>
<P>
After counting ballots on the spot, Han Dehua, a 35-year-old
farmer, was announced the winner as a deputy of the county
people's congress in the electoral district.
</P>
</TEXT>
