<HEADLINE> Vietnam's Leader Meets Chinese NPC Delegation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, November 24 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam hopes to strengthen
cooperation between its National Assembly and the
Chinese National People's Congress (NPC), said Nong Duc Manh,
chairman of the Vietnamese National Assembly here today.
</P>
<P>
Nong made the remark when meeting a delegation of the law
committee of the Chinese NPC, which arrived here last Thursday on
a good-will visit.
</P>
<P>
The frequent visits between the two countries' senior leaders
and exchanges between the Vietnamese National Assembly and the
Chinese NPC were evidence of continuing development of friendly
relations between Vietnam and China, Nong said.
</P>
<P>
He spoke highly of the great achievements the Chinese people
have made in the reform and opening-up drive under the leadership of
the Chinese Communist Party with Jiang Zemin at the core.
</P>
<P>
Xiang Chun, Chinese delegation head, said that as socialist
countries, China and Vietnam share a lot in common and exchanges
of experiences are in their interests.
</P>
<P>
He hoped that they will promote exchanges and deepen mutual
understanding and friendship. 
</P>
