<HEADLINE> Philippine Military to Take Actions Against Rebels </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, November 24 (Xinhua) -- Chief of Staff of the
Philippine Armed Forces Arnulfo Acedera today ordered all military
commanders to conduct aggressive and preemptive operations against
the New People's Army (NPA) after a number of ambushes against the
police by the group.
</P>
<P>
Acedera said the military would conduct intensified
intelligence operations and patrols against the rebels.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, he gave orders for additional security of military
facilities and air reconnaissance cover for ground patrols and
other operations.
</P>
<P>
However, Acedera said he did not see any need for redeployment
of troops, dismissing the NPA's attacks as only desperate attempts
to gain advantages on the negotiating table.
</P>
<P>
Formal peace talks between the government and the rebel group
were suspended after the abduction of a police officer by the NPA
on October 30.
</P>
<P>
Acedera accused NPA founding chairman Jose Sison of
orchestrating a scenario wherein increased rebel attacks would
directly or indirectly convince the Dutch government that it
should grant him political asylum.
</P>
<P>
This is a logical conclusion resulting from Sison's directives
and messages intercepted by the military's intelligence, Acedera
said.
</P>
<P>
The NPA rebels have recently conducted several surprise attacks
against at least three police stations in the country, killing
some policemen and taking several others hostage.  
</P>
</TEXT>
