<HEADLINE> Bank of China HK Branch Marks 80th Birthday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, November 24 (Xinhua) -- The Bank of China Hong Kong
Branch, one of the note-issuing banks in Hong Kong, held a
cocktail reception today at the Hong Kong Convention and
Exhibition Center to celebrate its 80th anniversary.
</P>
<P>
For the past 80 years, the Bank of China Hong Kong Branch has
devoted itself to serving the industrial and commercial sectors as
well as the general public, Jiang Zuqi, vice-chairman and
executive vice president of Bank of China and chief executive of
the Hong Kong-Macao Regional Office, said at the gathering.
</P>
<P>
"The bank has established close relationships with various
sectors of the community through supporting different
infrastructural constructions and participating actively in
community projects," he said.
</P>
<P>
The Bank of China has made every effort to help maintain
financial stability, to promote Hong Kong as an international
financial center and to maintain its continuing prosperity and
stability, Jiang stressed.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said the bank has gone through periods of ups and downs,
and has grown up and strengthened steadily.
</P>
<P>
"The establishment of its solid foundation in Hong Kong was
attributable to the leadership of our head office, the drive for
excellence, the prudent operation and the strenuous efforts of our
management and staff," Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
"It was also made possible by the confidence, the trust and the
support extended to us by the Hong Kong Monetary Authority, our
banking associates and various sectors of the community," he
added.
</P>
<P>
Looking into the future, Jiang said that after Hong Kong's
return to the motherland, the principle of "one country, two
systems" is being successfully implemented, and the prospects for
Hong Kong are bright. He said the Bank of China will join hands
with friends from all industries to build up a brighter future.
</P>
<P>
Established in September 1917, the Bank of China Hong Kong
Branch is now a major subsidiary of Bank of China. It is a
rotating chairman bank of the Hong Kong Association of Banks.
</P>
<P>
Since China's implementation of the policies of reform and
opening up in the late 1970's, the business of the Bank has
recorded substantial expansion.
</P>
<P>
Comparing the business figures of 1996 and 1978, the Branch's
deposits have increased by 75 times, loans by 141 times, total
assets by 107 times and pre-tax profit by 82 times.
</P>
<P>
At present, the Branch has 39 sub-branches, more than ten
subsidiaries and a number of associated companies in the finance,
securities, insurance, leasing and consulting businesses,
providing a full range of financial services.  
</P>
</TEXT>
