<HEADLINE> Floods Kill 25 People in Uganda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, November 24 (Xinhua) -- Twenty-five people have been
killed in flood in Uganda since last Friday, local media reported
today.
</P>
<P>
Ten people have been killed in eastern Tororo district,
including two children who died in Doho Koli village, six fuel
smugglers who drowned in Balaba river at Uganda-Kenya border and
Hyalakot Swamp Korukatipe village separately.
</P>
<P>
In the eastern district of Mbale, another 15 people have been
identified. An earlier report said the flood had already killed
20 people in the district last Thursday. Electricity and running
water in the town were stopped.
</P>
<P>
In western Kasese district, 500 local people were displaced
due to the flood.
</P>
<P>
In south-western Kabale district, torrential rains have caused
landslides that disrupted the road linking Uganda and Rwanda.
</P>
<P>
Weather experts reminded people to pay attention to the
would-be landslides in the western and eastern parts of the
country later this month and in December.
</P>
<P>
"The soils are very loose after heavy rains. Landslides will
be a common feature in these areas and should be expected," said
Bwango Apuuli, commissioner for meteorological department.
</P>
