retail, coupled with concerns of food safety, market acceptance
and changing demands, present complex challenges to the companies
and countries involved, he noted.
</P>
<P>
Cooperation among countries is needed in legislation, food
labeling, standardization of production and bio-safety in order to
meet the challenges, he said.  
