<HEADLINE> New President for All-China Federation of Taiwan Compatriots </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 24 (Xinhua) -- The Sixth National Congress of
All-China Federation of Taiwan Compatriots ended here today, with
Yang Guoqing elected as new president of the federation.
</P>
<P>
Born in Taibei in 1936, Yang moved to Japan with his parents at
the age of four. He returned to China in 1953.
</P>
<P>
Yang became a doctor after he graduated from the Beijing
Medical Institute in 1960, and he also received a doctor of
surgery degree from the Kobe Medical University in Japan.
</P>
<P>
He served as director of Beijing Municipal Office for Overseas
Chinese in 1990, and was transferred to the post of vice-president
of the All-China Federation of Taiwan Compatriots in 1993.
</P>
<P>
After his election, Yang said that the current situation
provides a good opportunity for further development of the
relationship of the two sides of the Taiwan Straits. He will work
together with colleagues to inherit and spread the patriotic
tradition of the Taiwan federation.
</P>
<P>
Yang said the federation will act as a bridge for exchanges
between the government and the Taiwan group, and will always be a
warm family for all Taiwan compatriots. 
</P>
