<HEADLINE> Sino-American MBA Program Launched </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 24 (Xinhua) -- An MBA program jointly set up
by the People's University of China and the State University of
New York to train managers of Chinese enterprises was launched
here today.
</P>
<P>
The Sino-American master's in business administration (MBA)
program is sponsored by U.S-based Praxair, Inc, the largest
producer of gas for industrial purposes in America.
</P>
<P>
According to the plan, professors of the People's University of
China and their counterparts in the Business School of the State
University of New York will cooperate in developing an MBA program
for Chinese students.
</P>
<P>
Chinese students will spend two years at People's University,
and be educated by professors from the two universities in
English. They will then travel to the United States to finish the
last semester, and graduate from the Business School of New York
State University located in Buffalo, N.Y.
</P>
<P>
China will further reform state-owned enterprises, and the
specialized business education program will help a new generation
of Chinese managers to learn skills needed for today's market
economy, said Edgar Hotard, president of Praxair.
</P>
<P>
Praxair now has established five joint ventures in China and
two wholly owned enterprises. 
</P>
