<DOCNO> XIE19971124.0083 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> S. Korean Government Plans to Adjust Economic Program </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, November 24 (Xinhua) -- The South Korean government will
adopt a drastic belt-tightening budget and adjust three major
macroeconomic indices -- GDP growth, external balances and prices,
the government officials said today.
</P>
<P>
With the IMF's bailout loans for South Korea to revive the
faltering national economy, the government will also accelerate
industrial restructuring, narrow current-account deficits and
upgrade the competitiveness of financial institutions and other
local enterprises, said Minister of Finance and Economy Lim
Chang-yuel.
</P>
<P>
South Korea has applied for rescue loans of 20 billion
U.S. dollars from the IMF. But analysts say the total bailout for
South Korea will reach 70-80 billion dollars, including huge
contributions which may come from the United States and Japan.
</P>
<P>
The IMF delegation will start negotiations with South Korean
officials and is expected to demand Seoul to drastically cut down
its budget spending and raise tax rates.
</P>
<P>
The IMF is also expected to require Seoul to implement
stringent self-rescue plans covering from macroeconomy to
financial institutions, as it has done to Thailand and Indonesia
recently, experts said.
</P>
<P>
Officials of the Ministry of Finance and Economy said that it
is inevitable for the country to adopt these measures and that the
GDP growth for 1998 will be lowered from 6 percent to 4 percent,
with the current-account shortfalls dwindling to less than 5
billion dollars and consumer price lower than 5 percent.
</P>
<P>
In 1999 and 2000, the GDP growth will be limited to less than 5
percent and the annual consumer prices gains to less than 4
percent, they said.
</P>
<P>
The government budget for this fiscal year will be cut to less
than 5.6 percent and the government is seeking measures on such
problems as wages and layoffs that the macroeconomic retrenchment
will bring with. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
