<HEADLINE> Cholera Victims Increase in Mozambique </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, November 24 (Xinhua) -- Up to Sunday, Cholera has
killed 136 people in Mozambique since it broke out over two
months ago, with an average of two dying from the epidemic daily
in the past ten days, the newspaper Noticias reported today.
</P>
<P>
The Hospital Central de Maputo (HCM) in the capital has
hospitalized 644 cholera patients by Sunday, up from 350 patients
on November 17.
</P>
<P>
In the neighboring Gaza province, people suffering from
cholera has increased from 40 on November 17 to 60 on November
22.
</P>
<P>
Belgium, Spain and other countries have sent 33 tons of
lactato de Ringer to help cholera patients prevent dehydration.
</P>
<P>
It is reported that there are now about 150,000 to 200,000
cholera virus carriers in Mozambique. And it will take at least
4 months to wipe out the epidemic. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
