<HEADLINE> HK Launches New On-Line Financial Information Service </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, November 24 (Xinhua) -- Hongkong Telecom IMS
Netvigator, a major Internet service provider in Hong Kong, today
announced the launch of Hong Kong Stock Express 2.0.
</P>
<P>
This new version of Hong Kong Stock Express -- the flagship
service of Netvigator Financial Express (NFX) -- provides a more
speedy and comprehensive real-time, on-line financial information
service for investors to better manage their investments and
capitalize on market opportunities.
</P>
<P>
Built with Java technology, NFX Hong Kong Stock Express 2.0
offers an easier and faster access to real-time quotes of all
listed local stocks and warrants.
</P>
<P>
The service also features a complete range of new real-time,
on-line financial tools, which help investors keep better track of
stock performance and market changes.
</P>
<P>
"We are very pleased to introduce the upgraded NFX Hong Kong
Stock Express 2.0 on-line financial service to our customers,"
said William Lo, managing director of Hongkong Telecom IMS.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that the new NFX 2.0 version has been upgraded
using some of the latest Internet technologies and it includes new
features and content.
</P>
<P>
"The new NFX Hong Kong Stock Express 2.0 represents a major
step of Hongkong Telecom IMS Netvigator toward the provision of a
total financial intelligence engine for investors to proactively
plan and manage their investment," Lo said.
</P>
<P>
NFX Hong Kong Stock Express 2.0 users can now better monitor
and capitalize on market opportunities by building their own
investment portfolios and making performance analyses with new
tools such as real-time, on-line "Stock Information," "Teletext,"
"News," "On-Line Charting" as well as the "Personal Portfolio" and
"Reports" functions.
</P>
<P>
The new NFX Hong Kong Stock Express 2.0 also features a
standalone version, which has been designed to save significant
download time.
</P>
<P>
To access all the financial information on NFX Hong Kong Stock
Express 2.0, users simply have to double click on the Netvigator
Financial Express icon and type in their user ID and password,
without having to go to the NFX web site or open their browsers.
</P>
<P>
In addition to the new Hong Kong Stock Express 2.0 service,
Hongkong Telecom IMS Netvigator Financial Express has been
offering a range of other value-added on-line financial
information services covering the local and Asian-Pacific markets.
</P>
<P>
These include the SHK Stock Monitor which provides a library of
local stock and warrant trading information since 1988, Asia
Financial Express covering financial information of major
Asian-Pacific markets, Reuters's Hong Kong Investor which provides
an extensive mutual fund database, and NetTrack Financial Service
which provides an on-line financial newsletter and commentaries.
</P>
