<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, November 24 (Xinhua) -- The five-man Kenyan team took
the men's title in the Chiba international marathon road relay
race in Chiba, Japan on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Philip Mosima clocked the fastest time of 13 minutes 26 seconds
in the second five-kilometer leg, while John Gwako also timed the
fastest of 34:55 in the fifth 12.195 kilometers leg, bringing the
five Kenyans home in a combined time of 1:59:16.
</P>
<P>
The men's race is run over five legs. The first and third are
ten kilometers long, the second and fourth are five kilometers
long, with a final leg of 12.195 kilometers. The women's race is
run over six equal legs.
</P>
<P>
Japan took second in 2:00:55, followed by Australia in 2:01:21,
South Africa fourth in 2:01:59, New Zealand fifth in 2:02:07 and
Spain sixth in 2:02:30.
</P>
<P>
Japan won the women's relay for a sixth year running with a
total time of 2:14:05, defeating China into second in 2:17:20 and
Romania third in 2:18:13.
</P>
<P>
Ethiopia was fourth in 2:19:09 and Russia fifth in 2:19:51.
