<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China, Indonesia to Boost Ties Between Parliaments </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, November 24 (Xinhua) -- China and Indonesia today
expressed the hope that their parliaments would strengthen their
cooperation for the further development of relations between the
two countries.
</P>
<P>
Meeting visiting Vice Chairman of the Chinese National People's
Congress (NPC) Wang Hanbin here today, Indonesian House of
Representatives Speaker Harmoko said China and Indonesia are
playing an increasingly important role in Asia-Pacific and
international affairs and therefore it is of great significance
for the two legislatures to increase exchanges.
</P>
<P>
He hoped that the exchanges between the next generation of
Indonesians and Chinese, especially young legislators, would be
strengthened, thus pushing forward the development of the ties
between the two countries in the future.
</P>
<P>
Vice Chairman Wang said the relations between China and
Indonesia have achieved progress in various fields since the two
countries resumed diplomatic ties seven years ago. The
relationship between the leaders of the two countries is very
good, he added.
</P>
<P>
He emphasized that both China and Indonesia should actively
push their friendly relations into the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
Wang noted that the friendly inter-parliamentary ties are an
important part of the two countries' relations.
</P>
<P>
China's NPC has conducted smooth cooperation in various forms
with the Indonesian Parliament and inter-parliamentary
organizations in other Southeast Asian nations, he said.
</P>
<P>
Wang and his party arrived here on Sunday at the invitation of
the Indonesian Parliament for a week-long visit to Indonesia.
</P>
<P>
During the visit, Wang and his party will also meet with
Indonesian Vice President Try Sutrisno and some cabinet ministers
and visit some other places in the country.
</P>
<P>
Indonesia is the last leg of Wang's four-nation Southeast Asia
tour which has taken him to Thailand, Malaysia and Singapore.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
