<HEADLINE> Brazil Wins World Grand Champions Cup Volleyball </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, November 24 (Xinhua) -- Barcelona Olympic champions
Brazil overwhelmed hosts Japan in three sets for their fifth
consecutive victory and won the men's trophy at the World Grand
Champions Cup volleyball tournament here on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The Brazilians, who beat Atlanta Olympic champions the
Netherlands Saturday, went on to make a clean sweep by scoring a
15-5, 15-11, 19-17 victory to rank the top place in the six team
round robin event.
</P>
<P>
In the other matches of the day, Asian champions China spent
just two hours to edge Australia 15-12, 15-9, 13-15, 12-15, 15-13
while the Netherlands ousted Cuba 15-11, 16-14, 4-15, 15-8.
</P>
<P>
The Netherlands, Cuba and China ended the tournament with a 3-2
win-loss record, ranking second to fouth places respectively.
</P>
<P>
Japan finished 5th with one win and four defeats and Australia
was the 6th place with all five defeats. 
</P>
