<HEADLINE> China, Peru Sign Personnel Exchange Agreement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 24 (Xinhua) -- The governments of China and
Peru signed an agreement on personnel exchanges and co-operation at
the Great Hall of the People in Beijing today.
</P>
<P>
In accordance with the agreement, in the next three years, the
two countries will conduct personnel exchanges and cooperation in
such areas as mining, fisheries, agriculture, energy,
transportation, telecommunications, environment protection, public
health and the development of natural resources.
</P>
<P>
Director of China's State Bureau of Foreign Experts Affairs Wan
Xueyuan and Peruvian Ambassador to China Luzmila Zanabria Zshikana
signed the agreement on behalf of their respective governments.
</P>
<P>
State Councillor Li Guixian met with the ambassador before the
signing ceremony. He expressed appreciation for efforts of
Peruvian experts in training Spanish language professionals in
China.
</P>
<P>
He also expressed the belief that the agreement will produce
greater results in personnel exchanges between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Since personnel exchanges between the two countries began in
the 1960s, some 70 Peruvian experts have worked in China. 
</P>
