<HEADLINE> Australian Dollar Ends Weaker </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, November 24 (Xinhua) -- The Australian dollar
weakened today, bereft of directional cues with no local data
released and Japanese financial markets closed.
</P>
<P>
The local currency settled at 69.28 U.S. cents from a close of
69.46 U.S. cents last Friday.
</P>
<P>
Traders said market activity was subdued, largely because of a
lack of Japanese players as a result of a national holiday there.
</P>
<P>
However, the Australian dollar, along with other currencies,
did rise against the yen after it was announced that one of
Japan's four big brokerages had collapsed because of financial
difficulties.
</P>
<P>
Yamaichi Securities Co today filed a request with the finance
ministry to suspend business with a view to liquidation.
</P>
<P>
The Australian dollar was at 87.90 yen from 87.59 yen
previously, and at 1.2022 marks from 1.2003 marks in Sydney
yesterday.  
</P>
