<HEADLINE> Hang Seng China Enterprises Index Down </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, November 24 (Xinhua) -- Hang Seng China Enterprises
Index today fell 24.84 points to close at 832.92.
</P>
<P>
The Index, introduced in August 1995, tracks the overall
performance of China's 32 state enterprises listed on the Hong
Kong Stock Exchange.
</P>
<P>
Today's Hang Seng MidCap 50 Index dropped 5.55 points from the
previous session to close at 1,329.82.
</P>
<P>
Hang Seng MidCap 50 Index comprises 50 most actively-traded
stocks of middle capitalization companies on the local bourse to
help investors and fund managers diversify their portfolios.
</P>
<P>
Today's Hang Seng China-Affiliated Corporations Index fell
55.91 points to close at 1,983.47.
</P>
<P>
Hang Seng China-Affiliated Corporations Index tracks the
performance of 32 locally-listed companies with a significant
equity interest held by entities in China.
</P>
<P>
The three segmented Hang Seng indices are devised by Hang Seng
Index (HSI) Services Limited, a wholly-owned subsidiary of Hang
Seng Bank. 
</P>
