<HEADLINE> Turkish President Leaves for Visit to Romania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, November 24 (Xinhua) -- Turkish President Suleymen
Demirel said here today that he pays a one-day working visit to
Romania in a bid to further develop the existing relations in
every field between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Before his departure at Ankara Esenboga Airport, Demirel said
in his statement that he would hold talks with his Romanian
counterpart Emil Constantinescu, address a joint session of the
Romanian Parliament, and participate in the meeting of
Turkish-Romanian Working Council.
</P>
<P>
The Turkish president pointed out that Turkey is satisfied with
the existing bilateral ties, saying: "There is a great cooperation
potential, especially in the economic field, between Turkey and
Romania."
</P>
<P>
Turkey and Romania will contribute to peace and stability in
the Balkan region and will strengthen bilateral and multilateral
cooperation in the economic and political fields, he added.
</P>
<P>
He said that Turkey, as a member of North Atlantic Treaty
Organization (NATO), will provide support for Romania to join in
the regional body.
</P>
<P>
A customs cooperation agreement and a cultural program between
the two countries will be signed during Demirel's visit in
Romania. 
