<HEADLINE> Milan Kucan Reelected as Slovenian President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LJUBLJANA, November 23 (Xinhua) -- Milan Kucan was reelected to
another five-year term as Slovenian president today by an absolute
majority of voters.
</P>
<P>
The 56-year-old Kucan obtained more than 55 percent of the
votes, 99.88 percent of which have been counted, becoming
the second president of Slovenia since the country proclaimed
independence from the former Yugoslavia in 1991.
</P>
<P>
The incumbent President of the Assembly Janez Podobnik, was
left far behind in the campaign with only 18.42 percent of the
votes while the other six rivals of Kucan gained less than 10
percent of the votes each.
</P>
<P>
The polling turnout was about 70 percent. 
</P>
