<HEADLINE> Asia-Pacific Social Security Meeting Opens in Manila </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, November 24 (Xinhua) -- Some 250 social security
experts from the Asia-Pacific region gathered here today for a
four-day meeting to discuss trends and issues that affect the
operation and prospects of social security coverage.
</P>
<P>
Hector Inductivo, International Social Security Association
(ISSA) regional director, said the 11th ISSA Regional Conference
for Asia and the Pacific would focus on "significant demographic,
social and economic transformations which challenge the viability
of present social security schemes."
</P>
<P>
The ISSA has more than 340 member organizations in 130
countries.
</P>
<P>
Participants in the conference include experts on social
security, pension fund and health insurance system from
international organizations such as the International Labor
Organization and the World Bank.
</P>
<P>
The meeting is hosted by the Philippine Social Security System
and the Government Service Insurance System, which are ISSA member
organizations.  
</P>
</TEXT>
