<HEADLINE> Inflation Rate Down in Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, November 24 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lanka's inflation rate
dropped to 10.6 percent in October from 11.7 percent in September,
a Central Bank spokesman said today.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said the inflation rate, as indicated by the
Colombo Consumer's Price Index, went down by 1.1 percent from
September to October.
</P>
<P>
Also in October, general food prices rose marginally by 0.1
percent, he said.
</P>
<P>
The price increases in rice, red onions, pepper, coconuts and
many vegetables were partly offset by the price decreases of fresh
and dried fish, eggs, potatoes, sugar and coconut oil, the
spokesman added.  
</P>
