<HEADLINE> Terrorists Reportedly Responsible for Athens Blast </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, November 24 (Xinhua) -- The "Revolutionary Nuclei," a
terrorist group in Greece, was responsible for the powerful blast
which occurred in Athens Sunday night, said an unidentified man
today.
</P>
<P>
The man told this to Skai, a local private television station,
the semi-official Athens News Agency (ANA) reported.
</P>
<P>
The explosion of a home-made device seriously damaged the
offices of the Pan-National Democratic Union, a political movement
founded earlier this year.
</P>
<P>
Some homes, shops and the offices of the Greek Strategic
Studies nearby also suffered more or less damage.
</P>
<P>
The same group has claimed responsibility for a number of similar
blasts, including one in August which damaged the offices of
former Greek Minister of Public Order Stelios Papathemelis. 
</P>
</TEXT>
