<HEADLINE> China Northern Airlines to Get New Overseas Routes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, November 24 (Xinhua) -- China Northern Airlines will
have five new air routes going to Japan and the Republic
of Korea (ROK) beginning this year and early next year.
</P>
<P>
The Shenyang-Osaka, Shenyang-Sapporo, Harbin-Niigata,
Harbin-Seoul, and Dalian-Tomiyama routes have been approved by the
Civil Aviation Administration of China (CAAC).
</P>
<P>
This means that about 20 flights have linked northeastern
China with Japan, ROK, the Democratic People's Republic of Korea,
Russia, and Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
The five new routes will have one or two flights a week, and
air carriers in Japan and ROK will be invited to act as China
Northern Airlines' overseas operators to help arrange return
flights.
</P>
<P>
The new routes will help promote economic exchanges between
Japan, ROK and Northeastern China, where much Japanese and ROK
investment is concentrated.
</P>
<P>
China Northern Airlines has a fleet of about 100 aircraft and
150 domestic and overseas air routes.  
</P>
</TEXT>
