<HEADLINE> EDS: Updated With More Details hke --Chinese President Meets Australian Prime Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VANCOUVER, Canada, November 23 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President
Jiang Zemin said here today that China attaches importance to
developing relations with Australia, and that he hopes the two
countries will establish a lasting, stable and sound relationship
geared towards the 21st-century.
</P>
<P>
Jiang made the remarks at a meeting with Australian Prime
Minister John Winston Howard this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
The two leaders are here for the 5th APEC informal leadership
meeting scheduled for Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said that China-Australia relations have been growing
smoothly since the two countries forged diplomatic ties 25 years
ago. The two sides have cooperated well on international and
regional issues.
</P>
<P>
Recalling their two meetings in the past two years in Manila
and Beijing, both leaders agreed that the exchange of high-level
visits between the two countries has played an important role in
promoting bilateral ties.
</P>
<P>
Howard said the development of Australia-China relations made
much headway in the past year by expanding common ground while
putting aside differences.
</P>
<P>
Australian businessmen are willing to establish good
partnership with Chinese entrepreneurs and increase their
cooperation in public management, social security and the service
sector, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
