<DOCNO> XIE19971124.0153 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Builts Tomb for Calligraphy Brushes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, November 24 (Xinhua) -- China has built a
writing-brush tomb in the Forest of Imperial Steles in Tianjin, a
major coastal city in north China.
</P>
<P>
More than 1,000 used brushes of 80 famous modern Chinese
painters and calligraphers were encased in the tomb.
</P>
<P>
The base is 3 meters long, 4 meters wide, and 1.5
meters tall, and has a stele inscribed "Writing-Brush Tomb" on top.
</P>
<P>
The country's first writing-brush tomb was built during
the Tang Dynasty (618-907). Classical painters and calligraphers
were accustomed to making a grave to bury their used brushes as a
symbol of their contribution to art.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19971124.0154 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shanghai Reports Rapid Industrial Production Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, November 24 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai, China's leading
manufacturing center, had 452.3 billion yuan (56.5 billion US
dollars) in industrial output in the first ten months of this
year, an increase of 14.9 percent over the same period of 1996.
</P>
<P>
Industrial growth is expected to reach 15 percent for the whole
of this year. Exports of manufactured goods reached 74.6 billion
yuan during the January-October period, an increase of 25 percent
over the same period of last year.
</P>
<P>
In October, the city had 74.6 billion yuan in industrial
output, an increase of 2.5 billion yuan over the same month in
1996.
</P>
<P>
In the first ten months of this year, production value of
foreign-funded enterprises, including joint ventures, co-operative
enterprises, and wholely foreign-funded companies, grew by 24.8
percent this year, 20 percentage points higher than that of
state-owned firms.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, collectively-owned enterprises had 84.7 billion yuan
in industrial output, 17.5 percent more than for the same period
of 1996.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai is expected to have steady industrial growth for the
rest of this year, according to Vice-mayor Jiang Yiren. 
</P>
</TEXT>
