<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Guangdong's Economy Starts to pick up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, November 24 (Xinhua) -- Guangdong Province resumed
its economic growth momentum in October after a long lull.
</P>
<P>
Suffering a depression last year, Guangdong's economy began to
inch into the black in the first half of this year. But it
wasn't until October that province's economy showed clear progress
out of the economic doldrums.
</P>
<P>
The industrial sector generated 76.4 billion yuan (9.2 billion
U.S. dollars) in output in October, up 17.2 percent over the
corresponding period last year. The sales-to-output ratio in this
sector reached 96 percent, according to official statistics.
</P>
<P>
Retail sales in October were 25.8 billion yuan, up 15.2 percent
over the same period last year. However, the retail price index
dropped by 0.9 percent and the consumer price index increased by
0.7 percent.
</P>
<P>
In the first 10 months of 1997, retail commodity sales were
235.6 billion yuan (28.3 billion U.S. dollars), up 13.6 percent on
an annual basis.
</P>
<P>
In addition, Guangzhou's October foreign trade volume climbed
to 6.63 billion U.S. dollars. The accumulated volume in the first
10 months registered 58.7 billion U.S. dollars, up 23.5 percent
over the corresponding period last year.
</P>
<P>
The utilization rate of foreign capital also picked up. In
October, 1.7 billion U.S. dollars had been spent, up 44.8 percent
over the same period last year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
