<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Aquatic Products Export Center Built In East China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, November 24 (Xinhua) -- China's Jiangsu province has
become an important export base of crabs, soft-shelled turtles,
and lobsters destined for Japan, the Republic of Korea, and Hong
Kong.
</P>
<P>
The province has 100,000 hectares of crab raising areas that
produce an annual output of 40,000 tons of fresh water crabs,
accounting for 80 percent of the country's total. The crab raising
industry earns an annual of three billion yuan (375 million
U.S. dollars) for the province. The city of Dafeng exports 3,000
tons of lobsters every year.
</P>
<P>
The province has set up 150 soft-shelled turtle bases. Baoying
County plans to spend 50 million yuan on a large aquatic products
center, and the province expects to produce one million
soft-shelled turtles a year and earn 70 million yuan from them.
</P>
<P>
Foreign businesses have shown growing interest in the
processing of the aquatic products. Companies from Singapore
invested in the province's processing lines. In Hongze County
alone, more than 20 kinds of the processed aquatic products are
sold to the United States, Japan, the Republic of Korea, and Hong
Kong. 
</P>
</TEXT>
