<HEADLINE> Number Of PhDs In China Growing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 24 (Xinhua) -- China has 27,500 people with
PhD degrees, according to the State Council's Office of the
Academic Degree Committee.
</P>
<P>
Their statistics show that China has graduated 3.8 million
people with bachelor degrees, and 349,600 with master degrees
since the introduction of the academic degree system in 1981.
</P>
<P>
To guarantee the quality of education, China has developed
strict regulations for institutions with academic-degree-granting
status. The institutions must be re-certified by the country's
educational authorities every two years.  
</P>
