<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> S'pore Airlines, Lufthansa Form Alliance </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, November 24 (Xinhua) -- The Singapore Airlines and
Lufthansa announced here today the formation of a strategic
alliance that will provide passengers of both carriers with a wide
range of enhanced benefits.
</P>
<P>
After a year of discussion, a Memorandum of Understanding (MOU)
confirming the alliance was signed here today by the chief
executive officers of the two carriers.
</P>
<P>
The Singapore Airlines (SIA) said that the MOU covers a wide
area of commercial cooperation, including code-sharing, network
and schedule development, frequent flyer programs, product
development, ground-handling, customer service, information
technology, and cargo operations.
</P>
<P>
The alliance is said to be an expansion of a long-standing
commercial relationship between the two carriers. SIA and
Lufthansa first began working together in September 1989, when
they initiated a joint freighter service between Singapore and
Frankfurt.
</P>
<P>
The two airlines will further develop this commercial
relationship to include passenger services and they will expand
their passenger schedules to offer travelers more choices and
better connection times, they said.
</P>
<P>
Currently, both airlines operate daily round-trip passenger
flights between Singapore and Frankfurt. Four of SIA's daily
flights to Frankfurt go beyond to New York. From April 1998, each
airline plans to increase its frequencies between Singapore and
Frankfurt to ten flights per week from the present seven, offering
passengers alternative daytime departures from both cities, along
with the current late-night services, they said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19971124.0172 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Special Tours For Special People Being Offered In South China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, November 24 (Xinhua) -- Some smart tourist agents in
this capital city of Guangdong Province have come up with special
tours using the theme of love and family.
</P>
<P>
Tourist agencies recently began announcing packages for young
and middle-aged parents and their children with the slogan
"Showing Affection to Your Children", and this summer, 5,000
people responded.
</P>
<P>
Organizers have provided eight travel routes since the special
travel service started three years ago.
</P>
<P>
Parents used to think that taking children along with them on a
trip was inconvenient, according to local travel agencies. But, in
recent years, most parents want to give their children more
experience by taking them on outings.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, higher paychecks have also enabled young
urbanites to show more filial piety to their elderly parents, so
travel agences have organized "filial love" package
tours. Organizers of groups of elderly travellers carefully plan the
routes and the routine. Guides are also much more aware of how to
take care of their health needs.
</P>
<P>
According to recent travel statistics in Guangzhou, more of the
elderly traveled this year, accounting for nearly 30 percent of
the number of tourists.
</P>
<P>
Financial support from their children helps the elderly in
this, and "filial love" tours accounted for two-thirds of the
tours for the elderly.
</P>
<P>
Other special tours, like those for honeymooners, spouses, and
alumni are now being planned, according to local sources. 
</P>
</TEXT>
