<HEADLINE> Technological Exchanges Increases in Northeast Chinese Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, November 24 (Xinhua) -- Liaoning Province, an old
industrial base in northeast China made 2.4 billion yuan (300
million US dollars) worth of technological transactions in 1996,
eight times the figure of a decade ago.
</P>
<P>
After China passed its Technical Contracts Law in 1987,
Liaoning worked out a series of regulations on the technology
market, contracts, consultation, and other areas.
</P>
<P>
By 1996, the province had established over 5,000 organizations
engaged in technical exchanges and had a state-level technical
exchange in Shenyang, the provincial capital, and two permanent
technology markets in the cities of Fushun and Jinzhou.
</P>
<P>
The province also has 14 pilot counties for developing
technology markets in rural areas.  
