<HEADLINE> Eastern Chinese Province Protects Wildlife </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, November 24 (Xinhua) -- Local government in China's
Anhui Province have made progress in protecting wildlife and
have returned 50,000 illegally-caught animals back to the wild in
the past two years.
</P>
<P>
Anhui has 50 varieties that are under state protection and 70
that have important scientific research value.
</P>
<P>
It has 16 nature reserves covering 244,000 ha., or 1.76 percent
of the province's total area, and has worked out regulations on
wild animal protection.
</P>
<P>
It has also penalized 1,000 restaurants and a dozen out-door
markets for illegally selling wild animals and confiscated more
than 20,000 kilograms of snakes and frogs.  
</P>
