<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 24 (Xinhua) -- Cotton Inc of the United
States, one of the world's largest cotton research and marketing
firms, has started operating in China to strengthen its presence
in the country, "China Daily" reported today.
</P>
<P>
The sole English newspaper in China said Cotton Inc has opened
its office in Shanghai to provide technical and market
information to Chinese mills, manufacturers and retailers, which
primarily use cotton imported from the United States.
</P>
