<HEADLINE> Figures on Beijing's Residential Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
He said investment in Beijing's real estate sector slid 4.3
percent, and sales dropped 4.6 percent.
</P>
<P>
"The investment was sufficient, although it declined slightly,"
Deng said.
</P>
<P>
The decline in investment was a result of the developers'
intention to lessen the investment scale stemming from the market
presure, he said.
</P>
<P>
"Developers were still confident about the city's property
market," he said.
</P>
<P>
They broke ground on commercial houses totalling 3.55 million
square meters during the first 10 months, up 74 percent from a
year ago.
</P>
<P>
They also leased 115.2 ha, which doubled last year's figure.
</P>
<P>
According to Deng, the average price for residential properties
rose 10 percent, and individuals' purchasing of houses rose 57
percent.
</P>
<P>
The amount of floor space sold during the first 10 months rose
6.4 percent compared with the corresponding period of last year,
and the sales volume went up 7.3 percent. 
