Taliban, who now control some two-thirds of Afghanistan, to help
them enter Dostum's stronghold Mazar-e-Sharif in northern
Afghanistan in May this year, forcing Dostum to flee abroad.
</P>
<P>
But he turned against the Taliban militia only days later and
killed a large number of their fighters, said the reports.
</P>
<P>
The reports said Malik had moved to Maimana after Dostum
returned to Mazar-e-Sharif from a four-month exile in Turkey to
reclaim leadership of Uzbeks.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the reports said Dostum and the Taliban on Saturday
released nine captives from both sides in a swap of prisoners.
</P>
