<HEADLINE> India's Tire Exports Register Sharp Increase </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, November 24 (Xinhua) -- India's tire exports
increased by 24 percent in volume and 13.6 percent in value during
the first half of the current fiscal year (from April 1997 to
March 1998) over the same period last year, the local press said
today.
</P>
<P>
According to official statistics, tire exports from the country
during April-September this year have been estimated at 1.042
million valued at 3.6872 billion rupees (about 101 million U.S.
dollars) against 841,000 tires worth 3.2453 billion rupees (about
88.9 million dollars) last year.
</P>
<P>
Shipment of truck and bus tires, the backbone of the tire
industry in India, accounted for three-fourths of the total tire
exports registered in the first half of the current fiscal year.
</P>
<P>
During the period under review, a total of 783,000 truck and
bus tires were exported, a rise of nearly 20 percent over the same
period of the previous fiscal year.  
</P>
