Catriana Le May Doan by clocking 1:15.43 in Sunday's final.
</P>
<P>
Le May Doan, one day after setting two world records, added
another gold medal and a silver, equalling her new world mark of
37.90 in winning the 500, and finishing second to Witty in a
scintillating pairing in the 1,000.
</P>
<P>
Le May Doan clocked 1:15.71, with Germany's Franziska Schenk
third in 1:15.92.
</P>
<P>
Sabine Volker of Germany was second in 38.57 and Witty third in
38.70 in the women's 500m event.
</P>
<P>
The Canadian team won two gold medals, a silver and a bronze on
the day for a record World Cup output of 11 medals from one
competition.
</P>
<P>
Jeremy Wotherspoon of Canada completed a weekend sweep of the
men's 500 meters with a time of 35.77. Yasunori Miyabe of Japan
was second in 35.79 and Horii third in 35.90. 
