<HEADLINE> Jiang Zemin Meets New Zealand PM </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VANCOUVER, November 23 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang
Zemin met with New Zealand Prime Minister James Bolger here today.
</P>
<P>
The two sides exchanged views on the development of bilateral
relations and their cooperation at the Asia Pacific Economic
Cooperation (APEC) forum.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said he was very pleased to meet Bolger at the informal
APEC Leaders' Meeting here in Vancouver. This is the fifth meeting
between the two leaders.
</P>
<P>
Bolger said he is looking forward to visiting China after the
APEC meeting.
</P>
<P>
He expressed the hope that frequent contacts between leaders of
the two countries will play a positive role in the development of
bilateral relations.
</P>
<P>
Jiang told Bolger that Chinese Premier Li Peng is looking
forward to meeting him.
</P>
<P>
Bolger noted the rapid growth of the Chinese economy, saying
that his country staunchly supports China's entry into the World
Trade Organization at an earlier date.
</P>
<P>
The talks between the two countries have yielded satisfactory
results, Bolger told Jiang.
</P>
<P>
Jiang expressed thanks to Bolger, and hoped that the two sides
will continue to enhance cooperation in the future.
</P>
<P>
New Zealand attaches great importance to its ties with China,
which has become its fifth largest trading partner, Bolger said.
</P>
<P>
He said he hoped that the two countries' entrepreneurs will
further strengthen their collaborations.
</P>
<P>
Jiang and Bolger share the view that the prospects of Sino-New
Zealand economic and trade cooperation are bright.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, the two leaders also discussed the recent
financial turmoil in southeast Asia. 
