<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Foreign Investment in Argentina Drops </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, November 23 (Xinhua) -- Influenced by the current
financial turmoil in Asia, foreign investors in Argentina are
withdrawing their investment in finance and securities, leading to
a sharp drop of foreign investment in the country.
</P>
<P>
Statistics from the National Securities Commission showed
foreign investment in securities market dropped by 15 percent from
23.1 billion U.S. dollars in September to 17.1 billion dollars in
October.
</P>
<P>
The withdrawal of investment mainly took the form of massive
sell-off of Argentine public bonds and the shares of Argentine
companies.
</P>
<P>
Argentine economists said the turbulence in global stock
markets originated in Southeast Asia exerted less impact on
Argentina than the financial crisis in Mexico in 1994. However,
its long-term impact is expected to show up next year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
