<HEADLINE> Russia, Brazil Strengthen Economic Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, November 23 (Xinhua) -- Russia and Brazil have
agreed to cooperate in airspace, education, culture and other
fields.
</P>
<P>
The agreements were signed by the two nations during a four-day
visit by Russian Foreign Minister Yevgeny Primakov, who left here
today for Argentina to continue his Latin American tour.
</P>
<P>
Under the agreements, the two countries will establish a higher
governmental council led by Brazilian Vice-President Marco Maciel
and Russian Prime Minister Viktor Chernomyrdin, which will meet
regularly.
</P>
<P>
During his stay in Brazil, Primakov, the first Russian foreign
minister to visit Brazil after the disintegration of the Soviet
Union in 1991, met Brazilian President Fernando Cardoso, Maciel
and Foreign Minister Luis Lampreia and discussed cooperation in
trade, culture, science and technology and on other political and
economic issues.
</P>
<P>
The trip, Primakov's second in Latin America, will take him to
Colombia and Costa Rica after his visit to Argentia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
