<HEADLINE> 8 Killed in Sri Lankan Bus Accident </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, November 24 (Xinhua) -- Eight persons were killed and
18 others injured when a bus hurtled down a 50 feet precipice at
Randenigala in Central province of Sri Lanka Sunday morning, local
press reported today.
</P>
<P>
A total of 106 passengers were in the bus when the incident
took place at around 10:15 in the morning. Among the dead was an
infant.
</P>
<P>
The injured were rushed to nearby hospitals in Kandy and
Badulla, two major cities in the province.
</P>
<P>
The reports quoted police as saying that the bus went off the
road when it tried to give way to two oncoming vehicles which were
attempting to overtake each other. 
