<HEADLINE> Thai Police to Act on Hiring of Illegal Alien Workers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, November 24 (Xinhua) -- Thai police are to take action
against employers who hire illegal alien workers, according to
Immigrant Division Commissioner Pol. Lt. Gen. Chidchai Wanasathit.
</P>
<P>
Police have to take action because of the rising number of
crimes committed by illegal alien workers, Chidchai was quoted
today by local press as saying.
</P>
<P>
There are only about 350,000 illegal alien workers registered
with the authorities. However, there are more than 400,000 who
have not reported to officials, he said.
</P>
<P>
He said murder is the most common crime committed by these
workers while the crimes involve both employers and illegal alien
workers.
</P>
<P>
Chidchai said that enforcing the law against local employers
should be the most efficient way of dealing with the issue.
</P>
<P>
Apart from facing a criminal suit, suspected employers will
also be liable to meet the expenses of returning such illegal
workers back home.
</P>
<P>
Chidchai said he will cooperate with border patrols and the
provincial police as well as the Central Investigation Bureau to
monitor the illegal entry of foreign workers.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
