<HEADLINE> Chinese Buyers Prop Up Shanghai's House Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, November 24 (Xinhua) -- Houses designed for domestic
buyers are playing a major role in Shanghai's real estate
business, today's China Daily reported.
</P>
<P>
The prices for Shanghai's houses are among the highest in
China, said Alex Wong, managing director of Shanghai Fortuneland
Property Consultants Co., Ltd..
</P>
<P>
But housing prices here are reasonably distributed, and buyers
have several alternatives.
</P>
<P>
Housing prices within the inner ring road could reach 6,700
yuan (about 807 U.S.dollars) per square meter and the figure is
as high as 10,000 yuan (about 1,200 U.S.dollars) per square meter
when it comes to the housing area near the city center.
</P>
<P>
In the suburbs, housing sells at 1,000 yuan (about 120
U.S. dollars) per square meter.
</P>
<P>
Wong pointed out that major purchasing hot spots continue to be
houses around the city center, and the prices of middle-price
housing around the inner ring road have seen a steady increase.
</P>
<P>
Wong said that during 1997 and 1998, 202,000 more square meters
of housing will go on sale.
</P>
<P>
He also predicted that residential buildings in the Pudong area
have started to catch public attention, among which those in the
Changli area have shown rich potential for large profits and
investments. 
</P>
</TEXT>
