<HEADLINE> Norway Takes World Cup 40-kilometer Ski Relay </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, November 23 (Xinhua) -- Norway took an easy victory
over Finland on Sunday in a 40-kilometer World Cup cross-country
ski relay in Beitostolen, Norway.
</P>
<P>
Norway clocked one hour, 37 minutes and 31.0 seconds, 3.6
seconds ahead of the ruuner-up Finland.
</P>
<P>
Dahlie, who won a personal record of 38th individual victory in
the 10 kilometers event on Saturday, clocked the third fastest
time while compatroit Erling Jevne, the third leg, stormed the
fastest time of the day.
</P>
<P>
Russia won the women's 20 kilometers classical-style relay in
53:37.1, follwed with Norway far behind as second and Italy
third. 
</P>
