<HEADLINE> Indonesian President's Call to Restore Ailing Stock </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, November 24 (Xinhua) -- Securities Analysts here hail
President Soeharto's instruction to state-owned companies to boost
their portfolio investment in order to help restore the ailing
stock market.
</P>
<P>
"It is really good news for investors. I think it will help
bring back the buying impetus," Vice President of Mashill Jaya
Securities Tjandra Kartika said Sunday.
</P>
<P>
He said although it will take several days for the state-owned
companies to comply with the president's instruction, the impact
of the order will be psychologically significant enough to renew
trading activities.
</P>
<P>
Last Friday, Soeharto instructed state-owned companies to
allocate at least one percent of their profits to buy shares on
the local stock market to help restore the weak trading
activities.
</P>
<P>
The president also instructed the monetary authorities to use
the 5 billion U.S. dollar standby loan from Singapore as
low-interest credits to improve the liquidity of big and medium
companies.
</P>
<P>
Tjandra said with a total profit of about 6 trillion rupiah
(1.7 billion dollars) last year, the country's state-owned
companies would have about 60 billion rupiah (18.75 million
dollars) to buy stocks.
</P>
<P>
"Such an amount is still small compared to the current market
capitalization of around 150 trillion rupiah (46.875 billion
dollars)," local press quoted Tjandra as saying.
</P>
<P>
There are 178 state-owned companies operating in Indonesia.
</P>
<P>
Indonesia's Jakarta Stock Exchange (JSX) composite index
declined by almost 45 percent from its peak of 740 points on July
7 to 391.25 points last Friday. At least 70 Shares declined below
their par value of 500 rupiah.
</P>
<P>
The composite index broke the psychological barrier of
400-point level last week on a combination of regional weakness,
currency crisis and lack of confidence in the country's financial
and capital market.
</P>
<P>
Some analysts said that without a bailout measure, the JSX
composite index could fall further to below the 350 level because
the market fundamentals remained very weak.  
</P>
</TEXT>
