<HEADLINE> Cabinet Reshuffle in Portugal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LISBON, November 23 (Xinhua) -- Portugal's Prime Minister
Antonio Guterres has in a major cabinet reshuffle appointed new
ministers for defense, the interior, economy and employment, the
Prime Minister's Office said today.
</P>
<P>
Jose Veiga Simao, 68, who once served as a minister in the
government of Marcello Caetano before 1974, became defense
minister.
</P>
<P>
Jorge Coelho, deputy minister at the Prime Minister's Office,
was appointed as interior minister to replace Alberto Costa, while
keeping his existing responsibilities.
</P>
<P>
Minister for Solidarity and Social Security, Eduardo Ferro
Rodrigues, will combine his job with that of employment minister.
</P>
<P>
The Economy Ministry will be headed by a close Guterres aid
Joaquim Pina Moura, who replaces Augusto Mateus.
</P>
<P>
A communique of the Prime Minister's Office said the prime
minister created two new ministries -- Ministry of Parliamentary
Affairs and Ministry of Sports, Youth and Drug Abuse -- which will
be headed respectively by Antonio Costa and Jose Socrates.
</P>
<P>
As Guterres revoked the post of minister in the Prime
Minister's Office, Foreign Minister Jaime Gama has been lifted to
number two in the government.
</P>
<P>
The shake-up was triggered by the resignation of Defense
Minister Antonio Vitorino, who resigned Thursday amidst suspicions
that he had avoided paying some tax on a land deal several years
ago.
</P>
<P>
It is the first government reshuffle since the Socialist Party
came to power in October 1995. 
</P>
</TEXT>
