<HEADLINE> McRae Takes Lead in RAC Rally </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, November 23 (Xinhua) -- Colin McRae of Britain took the
early lead after the opening 10 stages of the RAC Rally in
Cheltenham, England on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
His flu-stricken rival and points leader Tommi Makinen of
Finland was back in sixth after the first day and struggling to
stay there.
</P>
<P>
The Scot, who won the championship two years ago and needs to
make up 10 points on the Finn in the final race, finished the
first of three days racing with a 15-second lead over another
Finn, Juha Kankkunen. Another former world champion, Carlos Sainz
of Spain, was a further four seconds back.
</P>
<P>
Makinen, barely able to speak because of a heavy attack of flu,
was 32 seconds behind as the drivers returned to Cheltenham after
10 stages taking in auto racing circuits at Silverstone and
Donington Park. Although a sixth place finish would just be
enough to take the title he is already tired and could easily be
caught by the drivers behind. 
</P>
