<HEADLINE> Novotna Wins Chase Championships </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, November 23 (Xinhua -- Jana Novotna of Czech Republic
won the season-ending Chase Championship by defeating Mary Pierce
of France 7-6 (7-4), 6-2, 6-3 here on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
With Sunday's victory, Novotna regained the No.2 ranking which
she lost to Lindsay Davenport of the United States after the
Advanta tour last Monday.
</P>
<P>
Pierce, who was named the WTA Tour Comeback Player of the Year,
opened the match with blistering groundstrokes to beat Novotna to
the net as she did when she shocked top-seeded Martina Hingis in
the quarterfinals. She took in charge through the first 12 games.
</P>
<P>
But Novotna served brilliantly during the entire match, served
into Pierce's body to stave off the first break point, then she
set the tune in the rest of the match.
</P>
<P>
A day earlier, Novotna also teamed with Lindsay Davenport to
win the doubles title, defeating France's Alexandra Fusai and
Nathalie Tauziat 6-7 (5-7), 6-3, 6-2.
</P>
<P>
During the post-match ceremony, Novatna bursted to tears as she
thanked her coach Hana Mandlikova. 
</P>
</TEXT>
