<HEADLINE> Southwest China Now Major Sugar Producer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, November 24 (Xinhua) -- South China's Guangxi Zhuang
Autonomous Region has become one of the world's leading sugar
producers and ranked No. 11 in cane sugar production.
</P>
<P>
Since 1992, the autonomous region has had a good sugarcane
harvest for five consecutive years and provided the country
with two million tons of commercial cane sugar.
</P>
<P>
It produced 2.35 million tons of cane sugar last year, compared
with 421,000 tons in 1980. The autonomous region has increased
its cane growing area this year and it has gotten help from
favorable weather conditions.
</P>
<P>
The autonomous region is expected to harvest 24 million tons
of sugarcane this year, and 2.5 million tons of sugar.
</P>
</TEXT>
