<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Lions Clubs to Help Province Battle Cataract Problems </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, November 24 (Xinhua) -- Zhejiang Province has
launched an ambitious program for aiding the blind.
</P>
<P>
SightFirst China Action, a long-term program by Lions Clubs
International in cooperation with the Chinese government, will
sponsor 20 medical groups to perform cataract surgery for 105,000
people in the next five years in rural areas with a high incidence
of cataracts.
</P>
<P>
The coastal province in eastern China has about 270,000 people
with eye disease, with half suffering from
cataracts. Ophthalmologists have performed 83,621 cataract
operations in the last 10 years, helping 98 percent of the
patients recover some of their eyesight.
</P>
<P>
Lions, the world's largest service organization with 43,500
clubs in 185 countries or geographic territories, will also help
the local governments establish ophthalmic clinics in county
hospitals and train ophthalmologists and assistants in cataract
surgery.
</P>
<P>
A province-wide survey also will be conducted to determine the
development and distribution of the disease. Officials said the
survey will provide information to help set up a data base of eye
diseases. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
