<DOCNO> XIE19971124.0249 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Evening Newspapers Gain Popularity in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, November 24 (Xinhua) -- Three evening newspapers in
China have passed the one-million mark in daily circulation, according
to statistics released by the National Evening Newspaper
Association.
</P>
<P>
The three papers are Shanghai's "Xinmin Evening News,"
Guangzhou's "Yangcheng Evening News" and Nanjing's "Yangtze
Evening News".
</P>
<P>
"Today's Evening News" in Tianjin and three other evening
newspapers distribute more than 500,000 copies a day, while 22 others
publish from 100,000 t0 500,000 copies.
</P>
<P>
Among the existing 143 evening newspapers in China, 124 have a
combined daily circulation of 21 million copies.
</P>
<P>
About 46 percent of the 124 papers distributed the newspapers
themselves, statistics show.
</P>
<P>
Most of the publishers and distributors showed a profit, with
the largest earning more than 200 million yuan (24 million
U.S. dollars) a year.
</P>
<P>
</P>
</TEXT>
