<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shanghai Takes Steps to Solve Environmental Problems </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, November 24 (Xinhua) -- The municipal government of
Shanghai has strengthened its environmental administration and
enforcement to cope with the city's worsening environmental
situation.
</P>
<P>
"The general environmental quality of the city has leveled
off," said Shen Yonglin, an official with the city's
Environmental Protection Bureau. "Some parts of the city and some
environmental indicators have shown signs of improvement."
</P>
<P>
"As a 100-year-old industrial city and a city experiencing a
period of booming construction, Shanghai is facing a serious
challenge to protect its environment," Shen said.
</P>
<P>
The municipal government has kept a close watch on the city's
enviroment protection, he said. Leading officials at all levels
meet twice a year to discuss the problems and work out an annual plan
for environmental protection. They also inspect environmental
projects.
</P>
<P>
As many as 21 regional regulations and laws concerning
enviromental protection have been worked out in the past five
years. Six billion yuan (400 million U.S. dollars) has been
allocated to reduce pollutants and move polluting factories. A
total of 850 polluting factories have been moved from downtown
Shanghai or forced to suspend operation.
</P>
<P>
The first phase of a waste water treatment project for the
Suzhou River has been put into operation at a cost of 1.6 billion
yuan. The second phase of the project is now under construction.
</P>
<P>
The second phase of the diversion work for the Huangpu River is
expected to improve the city's drinking water quality. Estimated
cost of the project is 2.6 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
With the completion of the second phase of the Pudong Gashouse,
the Shidongkou Gashouse, and the Shanghai Coking Plant, more than
90 percent of the city's residents have access to natural gas.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19971124.0256 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-24 </DATE_TIME>
