<DOCNO> XIE19971124.0268 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Defense Industry Conversion Attracts Foreign Investors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, November 24 (Xinhua) -- Southeastern China's defense
industry has absorbed about 300 million U.S. dollars of foreign
funds for 90 joint ventures in their conversion from military to
civilian production.
</P>
<P>
Incomplete statistics show that foreign investors in this
mountainous region mainly come from Japan, Germany, the United
States, Britain and the Republic of Korea. The joint ventures are
engaged in such fields as car parts, motorbike components,
aircraft parts, household electrical appliances, chemicals,
electronics, textiles and food.
</P>
<P>
One of the largest projects is Chang'an Suzuki Automobile Ltd.,
which was jointly established by the Suzuki Co. Ltd. from Japan
and two Chongqing military enterprises. Suzuki invested 85 million
U.S. dollars in the venture.
</P>
<P>
Zhang Peikun, an official from the State Planning Commission
said that China's military industry in the southwestern region
started producing products for civilian use in the early 1980s,
"pulling off its mysterious veil."
</P>
<P>
The central government encouraged the shift from military to
civilian production by allowing them to move out of valleys and
into cities or near railways so that their products would be more
accessible to the market, he said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19971124.0269 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sino-German Pharmaceutical Firm Begins Operations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, November 24 (Xinhua) -- Tianjin Hexal Co., Ltd., a
joint venture between Germany's Hexal and Tianjin Limin
Pharmaceutical Company, has begun operations here.
</P>
<P>
The joint venture is the second pharmaceutical firm granted
GMP authentication in this port in northern China.
</P>
<P>
At a cost of 10 million U.S. dollars, the joint venture will
produce pain-killers and medicine for cardiac infarctions,
diuresis, hypertension and cirrhosis.
</P>
<P>
Tianjin Hexal is the first investment by the German firm, a
leading European pharmaceutical company. The upgrading of
workshops, equipment installation and staff training were started
in March last year and completed in September this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
