<DOCNO> XIE19971124.0271 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> French Socialists Conclude Congress </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, November 23 (Xinhua) -- The French Socialists today
ended their congress in the western port city of Brest with an
emphasis on the success scored by the Socialist Party under Lionel
Jospin in the legislative elections this year and the government
it established.
</P>
<P>
This is the first congress held by the Socialists since the
death of Francois Mitterrand in January 1996 and under Jospin.
</P>
<P>
The number two of the Socialist Party, Francois Hollande, said
that the congress is one of "pride" and "coherence" between the
political slogans of yesterday and today.
</P>
<P>
He praised Jospin for making the Socialist Party one of
"victory, rally and pride" which has overcome the inner fighting
it once experienced.
</P>
<P>
Jospin said in his closing speech that he himself is proud of
the course he has trailed through and the action he has taken, but
said that he remains cool.
</P>
<P>
The national secretary of the French Communist Party, Robert
Hue, whose party has been given three government seats by Jospin
in exchange for its support, also went to the congress to
congratulate, the first such gesture by the Communist leader in
history. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
