<BODY>
<HEADLINE> State Minister Says Germany Will Privatize </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, November 23 (Xinhua) -- Germany was to privatize more of
its major airports, press reports quoted a senior state official
as saying today.
</P>
<P>
The German government was planning to sell its partial stakes
in Cologne-Bonn, Hamburg, Berlin and Frankfurt airports, Wolfgang
Clement, economic minister of the state of North Rhine Westphalia,
told news weekly Focus in an interview in Duesseldorf.
</P>
<P>
Clement said he was told this by Federal Transport Minister
Matthias Wissmann. North Rhine Westphalia and the federal
government would move together by the end of December to sell
Cologne airport.
</P>
<P>
Privatization would ensure the airports were internationally
competitive, he added.  
</P>
</TEXT>
